# Global caches — extra cache mounts applied to every sbx session,
# regardless of flavor. Layered: <flavor>/caches (flavor author) ->
# ~/.config/sbx/caches (this file) -> .sbx/caches (per-project). Later
# layers override earlier ones on the same container path.
#
# Tool-specific caches should live in that flavor's own `caches` file
# (next to its Dockerfile), not here. Use this file only for caches
# that span flavors (e.g. tools you call from multiple flavor shells)
# or to override a flavor's cache choice without editing the flavor.
#
# Syntax (one per line, `#` comments allowed):
#   <host_rel>                            host bind, container = /home/dev/<host_rel>
#                                         (host_rel is relative to your host $HOME)
#   <host_rel>:<container_path>           host bind, explicit container path
#   @<volume_name>:<container_path>       named docker volume (user-owned; sbx clean
#                                         won't auto-delete it)
#
# Missing host paths are auto-created on first run.

# Cross-flavor caches (uncomment what you actually use):
# .cache/pre-commit                       # pre-commit framework
# .cache/pip                              # python — if you run pip from multiple flavors
# .cache/uv                               # uv / ruff
# go/pkg/mod                              # go modules — GOMODCACHE
# .cache/go-build                         # go build cache — GOCACHE
# .cache/deno

# Override a flavor's cache choice by matching its container path. Example:
# the `java` flavor binds your host's ~/.m2 by default; swap to an isolated
# docker volume here without editing the flavor:
# @sbx-maven-isolated:/home/dev/.m2
